[33mcommit 743e7efdaf40a194499b3375b3ce55a6ec1bea2c[m
Merge: f1f707863b 5c195a8b01
Author: StellarBot <contact@stellar-group.org>
Date:   Mon May 29 12:44:09 2023 +0000

    Merge #6263
    
    6263: Adding support for reading json configuration files for command line options r=hkaiser a=hkaiser
    
    Fixes: #6261
    
    This new feature is enabled by adding the `-DHPX_COMMAND_LINE_HANDLING_WITH_JSON_CONFIGURATION_FILES=On` configuration constant to the CMake command line. The parsing of the JSON file is performed using the JSON library available here: https://github.com/nlohmann/json. Add `-DHPX_WITH_FETCH_JSON=On` to automatically fetch and install it with HPX.
    
    Note: JSON configuration files must have the file extension `.json`. They can be passed to any HPX application either as:
    ```
    ./app `@some_config_data.json`
    ```
     or by using the explicit `--hpx:options-file` command line option, e.g.
    ```
    ./app --hpx:options-file=some_config_data.json
    ```
    
    This extracts key/value pairs from arbitrary levels in the JSON file, composing the option names from the keys. For instance:
    ```
    {
        "option1": 42,
        "option2": 42.0,
        "option3": [ 1, 2, 3 ],
        "option4": true
        "base": {
            "option5": 42
        }
    }
    ```
    would be equivalent to writing:
    ```
    ./app --option1=42 --option2=42.0 --option3=1 --option3=2 --option3=3 --option4 --base:option5=42
    ```
    
    
    Co-authored-by: Hartmut Kaiser <hartmut.kaiser@gmail.com>

